# React UI Components

## Component Style

- Functional components only; named exports for phase components.
- Props typed inline or as `interface XxxProps` above component.
- Avoid redundant state; derive from `useLiveQuery` or props where possible.

## Styling

- Tailwind utility classes; theme tokens in `@src/index.css` `@theme` block.
- Use `@tailwindcss/typography` `prose` for rich text areas (TipTap).
- Icons from `lucide-react`; animations via `motion/react`.

## TipTap Editor

- Editor confined to `@src/components/phases/WritingPhase.tsx` and `@src/components/writing/EditorToolbar.tsx`.
- Do not mount TipTap in other phases without ADR justification.

## i18n

- All user-visible strings via `useLanguage()` → `t('key')` from `@src/i18n/translations.ts`.
- Add both `en` and `de` keys for new UI copy.

## Accessibility

- Icon-only buttons require `aria-label`.
- Maintain visible focus states; support keyboard navigation in modals/menus.
- `CommandPalette` and nav items must be reachable by keyboard.

<example>
<button aria-label={t('nav.settings')} onClick={onOpenSettings}>
  <Settings className="h-5 w-5" />
</button>
</example>

<example type="invalid">
<button onClick={onOpenSettings}>
  <Settings className="h-5 w-5" />
</button>
</example>

## Phase Shell

- `App.tsx` owns phase `switch`; new phases register in sidebar + bottom nav.
- Shared layout: `Sidebar`, `RightPanel`, `BottomNav` — keep phase components free of shell duplication.

## Error UX

- Wrap risky subtrees with `@src/components/ErrorBoundary.tsx`.
- Async failures: `toast.error()` from sonner.
